data.text:
2013 Senior Season

• Threw for his first two touchdown passes during the loss at South Alabama, he finished with a career high 181 yards passing as well as a career high 106 yards rushing

• Made his first career start at South Alabama

• Completed his first pass of the season and finished 5-8 during the loss at Penn State

2012 Junior Season

• Appeared in nine games

• Completed 14-of-23 passes for 230 yards and a touchdown

• Ran for 31 yards

• Career-high 93 yards passing in the 23-7 win at Buffalo

• In first game with the Golden Flashes he was a perfect 3-for-3 for 84 yards and a 63-yard touchdown pass in 41-21 victory over Towson

Prior to Kent State

• Named 2011 National Southern Conference Co-Offensive Player of the Year

• Completed 184-of-333 passes for 2,539 yards and 27 touchdowns in 2011

• Also ran for 403 yards and seven touchdowns

• Led Palomar to 7-4 record and an appearance in the Southern California Community College semifinals

• Played first season of college football at Nevada

• Earned All-Palomar Conference First Team honors in junior and senior seasons at Vista H.S.

Personal

• Born Dec. 8, 1990

• Son of Mario and Phenella Adame

• Has one sister, Phenesse

• Majoring in business administration and sports administration
